00:40.375 --> 00:46.043
<i>~ Of my favorite things ~</i>

00:48.413 --> 00:51.711
We were somewhere around
Barstow, on the edge of the desert...

00:51.768 --> 00:54.108
when the drugs
began to take hold.

01:05.847 --> 01:08.666
I remember saying something like:

01:08.734 --> 01:12.022
I feel a bit lightheaded.
Maybe you should drive.

01:14.649 --> 01:17.948
- Hmm ?
- Suddenly there was
a terrible roar all around us...

01:18.006 --> 01:20.825
and the sky was full of
what looked like huge bats...

01:20.893 --> 01:23.703
- all swooping and screeching
and diving around the car.

01:23.770 --> 01:26.637
- And a voice was screaming:
- Holy Jesus, what are
these goddamned animals ?

01:26.714 --> 01:30.511
<i>~ Come on, baby ~</i>

01:30.588 --> 01:32.918
- Did you say something ?
- Hmm ?

01:32.985 --> 01:34.836
Never mind.

01:34.903 --> 01:36.754
It's your turn to drive.

01:36.821 --> 01:39.641
No point in mentioning
these bats, I thought.

01:39.708 --> 01:42.451
The poor bastard'll
see them soon enough.

01:42.518 --> 01:44.378
<i>~ Baby, I'm startin'
to feel human ~</i>

01:44.436 --> 01:46.891
<i>- ~ Ohh, ohh, yeah ~
- ~ Hey, hey, Feel with me, baby ~</i>

01:46.968 --> 01:49.720
<i>~ 'Cause I feel it comin' on ~</i>

01:52.184 --> 01:54.735
Fucking pigs ! Flying !

01:57.689 --> 01:59.598
We had two bags of grass...

01:59.674 --> 02:01.525
75 pellets of mescaline...

02:01.592 --> 02:04.488
five sheets of
high-powered blotter acid...

02:04.565 --> 02:06.953
a salt shaker
half-full of cocaine...

02:07.030 --> 02:10.098
a whole galaxy of multicolored
uppers, downers, screamers, laughers.

02:10.164 --> 02:13.944
Also a quart of tequila,
a quart of rum, a case of beer...

02:14.011 --> 02:15.861
- a pint of raw ether...
- Shit !

02:15.929 --> 02:17.780
two dozen amyls.

02:17.847 --> 02:19.948
Not that we needed all that
for the trip...

02:20.024 --> 02:22.834
but once you get locked into
a serious drug collection...

02:22.901 --> 02:25.289
the tendency is to push it
as far as you can.

02:26.613 --> 02:29.432
The only thing that really
worried me was the ether.

02:29.489 --> 02:32.624
There is nothing in the world
more helpless and irresponsible
and depraved...

02:32.691 --> 02:35.511
than a man in the depths
of an ether binge...

02:35.569 --> 02:38.388
and I knew we'd get into
that rotten stuff pretty soon.

02:40.690 --> 02:41.582
A House subcommittee report
says illegal drugs killed...

02:41.649 --> 02:44.402
160 American G.I.s
last year...

02:44.469 --> 02:46.579
40 of them in Vietnam.

02:47.509 --> 02:48.716
<i>- ~ One toke over the line
Sweet Jesus ~</i>

02:48.783 --> 02:50.644
One toke, man !

02:50.711 --> 02:53.742
<i>[ Singing Along With Radio,
Slightly Behind ]
~ One toke over the line ~</i>

02:53.809 --> 02:56.878
<i>~ Sittin' downtown
at a railway station ~</i>

02:56.945 --> 02:59.601
<i>~ One toke over the line ~</i>

02:59.668 --> 03:02.123
<i>- One toke, you poor fool ?
- ~ Sweet, sweet Mary ~</i>

03:02.200 --> 03:04.876
Wait'll you see
those goddamned bats, man.

03:04.943 --> 03:06.833
<i>~ Mine ~</i>

03:06.900 --> 03:09.449
<i>~ One toke over the line ~</i>

03:11.119 --> 03:14.571
- Let's give that boy a lift.
- What ? No !

03:14.638 --> 03:16.498
Wait !

03:16.566 --> 03:19.184
We can't stop here.
This is bat country.

03:22.512 --> 03:26.290
Hot damn ! I never rode
in a convertible before !

03:26.357 --> 03:29.674
Is that right ? Well, I guess
you're about ready then, aren't ya ?

03:29.742 --> 03:33.041
We're your friends. We're not
like the others, man. Really.

03:33.108 --> 03:35.956
No more of that talk, or I'll
put the leeches on you. Understand ?

03:38.575 --> 03:40.109
Get in.

03:43.533 --> 03:46.736
How long could we maintain,
I wondered.

03:46.803 --> 03:50.246
How long before one of us starts raving
and jabbering at this boy ?

03:50.322 --> 03:52.173
What will he think then ?

03:52.240 --> 03:56.229
This same lonely desert was the last
known home of the Manson family.

03:56.306 --> 03:59.567
Would he make that grim connection
when my attorney starts screaming...

03:59.634 --> 04:02.444
about bats and huge manta rays
coming down on the car ?

04:02.511 --> 04:06.155
If so, well, we'll just have to
cut his head off and bury him somewhere.

04:06.222 --> 04:09.521
- 'Cause it goes without saying
that we can't turn him loose.

04:09.588 --> 04:12.877
He'd report us at once to some kind of
outback nazi law enforcement agency...

04:12.944 --> 04:15.275
and they'll run us down
like dogs.

04:15.342 --> 04:19.120
- Jesus, did I say that,
or just think it ?
- Jesus, did I say that ?

04:19.188 --> 04:21.519
Was I talking ?
Did they hear me ?

04:21.586 --> 04:24.751
It's okay. Just admiring
the shape of your skull.

04:24.818 --> 04:27.628
- No, thanks !
- Maybe I'd better have
a chat with this boy.

04:27.694 --> 04:30.513
- I have asthma !
- Perhaps if I explain things,
he'll rest easy.

04:30.570 --> 04:32.431
All right, listen.

04:32.498 --> 04:36.037
There's one thing you should probably
understand-- Can you hear me ?

04:36.114 --> 04:37.898
Good.

04:37.965 --> 04:40.785
I want you to have
all the background.

04:40.842 --> 04:43.182
- Aah !
- This is a very ominous assignment...

04:43.249 --> 04:45.100
with overtones of
extreme personal danger.

04:45.167 --> 04:47.785
I'm a Doctor of Journalism.
This is important, goddamn it !

04:47.852 --> 04:50.086
This is a fucking true story !

04:50.153 --> 04:52.196
You fucking--

04:52.273 --> 04:54.757
Get your hands off my fucking head !

04:54.834 --> 04:58.622
- Now, now, now.
- Our vibrations were
getting nasty. But why ?

04:58.698 --> 05:01.039
Was there no communication
in this car ?

05:01.106 --> 05:03.915
- Had we deteriorated
to the level of dumb beasts ?

05:03.982 --> 05:06.313
This man at the wheel
is my attorney.

05:06.380 --> 05:09.678
He's not just some dingbat I found on
the Strip, man. He's a foreigner.

05:09.736 --> 05:13.217
I think he's probably Samoan.
It doesn't matter, though, does it ?

05:13.294 --> 05:15.624
- Are you prejudiced ?
Hell, no.

05:15.691 --> 05:17.542
I didn't think so.

05:17.609 --> 05:20.908
Because, in spite of his race,
the man is extremely valuable to me.

05:20.975 --> 05:24.265
- Oh, shit. I forgot about the beer.
You want some ?
- No.

05:24.332 --> 05:26.404
- How 'bout some ether ?
- What ?

05:28.494 --> 05:29.290
Never mind. All right, let's get right
to the heart of this thing.

05:29.357 --> 05:30.498
- Twenty-four hours ago
we were sitting...
- ...in the Pogo Lounge...

05:32.224 --> 05:36.156
of the Beverly Heights Hotel,
in the patio section, of course...

05:36.223 --> 05:39.542
drinking Singapore Slings
with mescal on the side...

05:39.618 --> 05:45.287
hiding from the brutish realities
of this foul year of our Lord, 1971.

05:45.344 --> 05:48.163
Cops were goin' apeshit--

05:48.230 --> 05:53.054
Perhaps this is the call you've
been waiting for all this time, sir.

05:53.121 --> 05:54.982
Perhaps.

05:55.039 --> 05:57.561
Yeah. Mm-hmm.

05:57.637 --> 05:59.489
Mmm ! Really. All right.

05:59.556 --> 06:01.944
Yeah ? Oh, yeah, yeah.
Oh, yeah.

06:02.021 --> 06:03.392
Okay. Bye.

06:03.459 --> 06:05.560
- That was headquarters.
They want me to--
- Ahem.

06:10.114 --> 06:11.965
Thank you.

06:13.154 --> 06:15.974
They want me to go
to Las Vegas at once...

06:16.031 --> 06:18.851
make contact with a Portuguese
photographer named Lacerda.

06:18.918 --> 06:20.768
He'll have
all the details.

06:20.836 --> 06:24.125
All I have to do is check into my
soundproof suite. He'll seek me out.

06:24.192 --> 06:26.811
- What do you think ?
- Sounds like real trouble.

06:26.878 --> 06:29.696
You're gonna need plenty of legal
advice before this thing is over.

06:29.764 --> 06:31.614
Oh, yeah.

06:31.681 --> 06:34.712
As your attorney, I advise you to rent
a fast car with no top.

06:34.788 --> 06:36.640
And you'll need
the cocaine.

06:36.707 --> 06:39.968
Tape recorder
for special music.

06:40.035 --> 06:41.885
Acapulco shirts.

06:41.952 --> 06:45.463
Get the hell out of L.A.
for at least 48 hours.

06:45.540 --> 06:47.389
- Blows my weekend.
- Why ?

06:47.457 --> 06:51.235
'Cause, naturally, I'm
gonna have to go with you.

06:51.293 --> 06:54.227
We're gonna have to
arm ourselves to the teeth.

06:54.304 --> 06:56.635
Well, why not ?

06:56.702 --> 07:00.279
I mean, if a thing's worth doing,
it's worth doing right.

07:01.506 --> 07:03.923
This is the American Dream
in action.

07:04.959 --> 07:06.455
Wait !

07:08.219 --> 07:12.535
Shit, we'd be fools not to
ride this strange torpedo
all the way out to the end.

07:12.612 --> 07:14.462
Indeed.
We must do it.

07:14.529 --> 07:16.438
What kind of story
is this ?

07:16.515 --> 07:18.365
It's the Mint 400...

07:18.432 --> 07:22.259
the richest off-road race for
motorcycles and dune buggies in
the history of organized sport.

07:22.335 --> 07:24.187
It's a fantastic
spectacle...

07:24.254 --> 07:26.105
in honor of some
fatback grosero...

07:26.172 --> 07:28.990
who owns the luxurious Mint Hotel
in downtown Las Vegas.

07:29.057 --> 07:31.321
At least that's what
the press release says.

07:31.388 --> 07:33.728
As your attorney,
I advise you to buy a motorcycle.

07:33.786 --> 07:37.085
How else can you cover
a thing like this righteously ?

07:37.152 --> 07:40.442
Well, we're gonna have to
drum it up on our own.

07:40.509 --> 07:42.369
Pure Gonzo journalism.

07:44.354 --> 07:46.809
Shit !

07:51.901 --> 07:55.200
Getting hold of the drugs
and shirts had been no problem...

07:55.257 --> 07:58.077
but the car and tape recorder were
not easy things to round up at 6:30...

07:58.144 --> 08:00.475
on a Friday afternoon
in Hollywood.

08:00.542 --> 08:03.323
Sounds beautiful.
Great. Hang on to it.

08:03.391 --> 08:06.200
Fuckin' A, the gentleman has
a major credit card !

08:06.267 --> 08:09.364
That's right, man. Don't take any guff
from these fucking swine.

08:09.431 --> 08:11.292
I just got through
saying that.

08:11.359 --> 08:15.444
Do you realize who the fuck
you're talking to ? Do you ?

08:15.511 --> 08:17.372
Be over in 30 minutes.

08:20.154 --> 08:22.387
We're gonna need a sound store.

08:22.455 --> 08:25.274
We won't make the nut
unless we have unlimited credit.
- We will, man.

08:25.341 --> 08:27.642
You Samoans
are all the same.

08:27.710 --> 08:32.466
You have no faith in the essential
decency of the white man's culture.

08:32.543 --> 08:34.394
The store was closed...

08:34.461 --> 08:37.270
but the salesman said
he could wait if we'd hurry.

08:39.256 --> 08:42.421
But we were delayed en route
when the Stingray in front of us
killed a pedestrian.

08:43.611 --> 08:46.428
We had trouble again
with the car rental agency.

08:46.486 --> 08:49.785
Mr. Duke, we're all settled.
If I could get your John
Hancock, you're on your way.

08:49.852 --> 08:53.459
- Yeah.
- You're gonna be real careful
with this car, right ?

08:53.526 --> 08:55.386
Oh, yeah, man.
Of course.

09:01.112 --> 09:03.932
Holy smokes !

09:03.989 --> 09:07.767
You just backed over
a 2-foot concrete abutment,
you didn't even slow down.

09:07.834 --> 09:10.797
What, were you going about,
uh, oh, I don't know,
45 miles an hour backwards ?

09:10.874 --> 09:12.724
- There's no harm done.
- Oh ?

09:12.791 --> 09:15.611
I always test the transmission that way,
the rear end for stress factors.

09:15.669 --> 09:18.488
- Boy, this is really a nice pen, man.
- Hey, uh, listen, you--

09:18.556 --> 09:21.366
you fellas haven't been,
uh, drinking, have you ?

09:21.433 --> 09:23.283
- No. Not me.
- Oh. Well--

09:23.350 --> 09:26.169
We're responsible people.

09:26.227 --> 09:28.088
Damn it,
you've got my pen !

09:29.430 --> 09:31.291
Goddamn hippies !

09:33.880 --> 09:37.774
We spent the rest of that night rounding
up materials and packing the car.

09:37.851 --> 09:40.661
Then we ate some mescaline
and went swimming.

09:42.713 --> 09:44.564
Our trip was different.

09:44.631 --> 09:46.480
It was to be
a classic affirmation...

09:46.548 --> 09:49.367
of everything right and true
in the national character...

09:49.434 --> 09:52.465
a gross physical salute
to the fantastic possibilities
of life in this country.

09:52.532 --> 09:54.393
But only for those
with true grit.

09:54.451 --> 09:56.723
And we are chock full
of that, man.

09:57.558 --> 09:59.121
Damn right !

09:59.188 --> 10:02.640
My attorney understands this concept,
despite his racial handicap.

10:02.708 --> 10:05.048
But do you ?

10:05.115 --> 10:09.199
He said he understood, but I could
see in his eyes that he didn't.

10:09.266 --> 10:12.115
He was lying to me.

10:13.333 --> 10:15.702
Ohh ! Aaah !

10:20.947 --> 10:23.728
Aaah ! Aaah !

10:23.795 --> 10:25.655
Ohhhhh !
Medicine !

10:25.713 --> 10:27.573
- What ?
- Medicine !

10:27.640 --> 10:30.220
Medicine ? Oh, yeah, medicine !
Right. Right here.

10:30.287 --> 10:33.107
Don't worry. This man has a bad heart.

10:33.174 --> 10:35.025
Angina pectoris.

10:35.093 --> 10:37.903
But we have a cure for it.
Here you go. All right.

10:37.970 --> 10:40.789
Big whiff. Big whiff.
Big whiff, sonny boy.

10:40.856 --> 10:43.666
Ah. There you go. Much better.

10:43.733 --> 10:46.187
Now for the doctor.

10:58.320 --> 11:00.180
What the--

11:00.247 --> 11:03.594
What the fuck are we doing out here
in the middle of the desert ?

11:03.670 --> 11:06.345
Somebody call the police.
We need help.

11:06.422 --> 11:09.318
- We need help.
We need help. We need help.

11:17.652 --> 11:19.503
The truth.

11:20.462 --> 11:22.323
Truth ?

11:22.390 --> 11:24.557
We're goin' to Vegas...

11:24.624 --> 11:29.064
to croak a scag baron
named Savage Henry.

11:29.141 --> 11:32.104
- It's true.
- Why ? Because I've
known him for years...

11:32.181 --> 11:34.032
but he ripped us off.

11:34.099 --> 11:36.468
And you know what that means.
- And you know what that means.

11:36.525 --> 11:38.347
- Right ?
- No.
- Mm-hmm.

11:38.414 --> 11:40.275
Savage Henry...

11:40.333 --> 11:42.193
has cashed
his check.

11:42.261 --> 11:45.069
- Cashed his check.
- And we're gonna rip his lungs out.

11:45.136 --> 11:48.301
- And eat them. That bastard
won't get away with this.

11:48.368 --> 11:51.178
I mean, what is going on
in this country...

11:51.245 --> 11:54.659
when a scum sucker like that
can get away with sandbagging
a Doctor of Journalism ?

11:55.859 --> 11:57.709
- Hey !
- Thanks for the ride !

11:57.776 --> 12:00.107
- Don't worry about me !
- Wait a minute !

12:00.174 --> 12:02.034
Come back
and have a beer !

12:02.093 --> 12:03.953
Shit.

12:04.020 --> 12:06.186
Fuck. I'm gonna miss him.

12:06.254 --> 12:08.593
- Move over !
- Did you see his eyes ?

12:08.651 --> 12:11.470
We have to get out of California
before that kid finds a cop.

12:11.537 --> 12:13.389
Scoot over,
you fat bastard.

12:13.456 --> 12:16.745
- We had a real freak on our hands !
- Oh, shit.

12:19.057 --> 12:22.250
It was absolutely imperative
that we get to the Mint Hotel...

12:22.318 --> 12:24.178
before the deadline
for press registration.

12:24.235 --> 12:27.370
Otherwise we might have to
pay for our suite.

12:32.943 --> 12:37.220
Jesus ! Did you see what God
just did to us, man ?

12:37.296 --> 12:39.627
God didn't do that.
You did it.

12:39.694 --> 12:41.545
You're a narcotics agent.
I knew it.

12:41.612 --> 12:45.063
That was our cocaine,
you fucking pig, swine, whore !

12:45.130 --> 12:47.365
You'd better be careful.

12:47.432 --> 12:51.115
Plenty of vultures out here that'll pick
your bones clean before morning.

12:51.182 --> 12:53.829
- You fucking whore.
- Hee hee hee.

12:55.057 --> 12:57.541
Here's your half
of the sunshine acid. Eat it.

12:57.608 --> 12:59.948
Yeah.

13:00.015 --> 13:01.866
Great.

13:01.933 --> 13:03.909
How long do I have ?

13:03.976 --> 13:06.795
As your attorney, I advise you
to drive at top speed...

13:06.862 --> 13:10.631
or it'll be a goddamn miracle
if we can get there before
you turn into a wild animal.

13:13.575 --> 13:15.368
<i>~ Yeah, yeah ~</i>

13:15.435 --> 13:17.286
Are you ready for that ?

13:17.353 --> 13:20.173
Checking into a Vegas hotel
under a phony name...

13:20.231 --> 13:23.654
with intent to commit capital fraud
and a head full of acid ?

13:23.722 --> 13:25.514
I sure hope so.

13:26.569 --> 13:29.091
Thirty minutes.
It was going to be very close.

13:34.030 --> 13:35.555
<i>~ Well, she's all
you'd ever want ~</i>

13:35.631 --> 13:37.224
<i>~ She's the kind
I'd like to flaunt ~</i>

13:37.291 --> 13:39.045
<i>~ And take to dinner ~</i>

13:39.113 --> 13:41.319
Welcome to the Mint Hotel !

13:41.386 --> 13:43.208
<i>~ Well, she always
knows her place ~</i>

13:43.276 --> 13:45.067
<i>~ She's got style
She's got grace ~</i>

13:45.135 --> 13:47.590
<i>~ She's a winner ~</i>

13:48.616 --> 13:51.340
<i>~ She's a lady ~</i>

13:51.407 --> 13:53.670
<i>~ Whoa-whoa-whoa
She's a lady ~</i>

13:53.738 --> 13:55.204
Hmm ? Mmm.

13:55.272 --> 13:58.312
<i>~ Talking about
my little lady ~</i>

13:58.379 --> 14:01.199
<i>- Come on, take the ticket.
We're busy here.
- ~ And the lady is mine ~</i>

14:01.256 --> 14:03.270
Come on, take the ticket.
Take it.

14:03.337 --> 14:05.197
Take the ticket.

14:05.254 --> 14:08.611
I need this. Right ?

14:08.688 --> 14:10.443
I'll remember your face.

14:12.428 --> 14:15.660
There is
no way of explaining the terror I felt.

14:17.319 --> 14:20.618
Attention,
all Mint Hotel guests.

14:20.685 --> 14:23.015
Will the owner
of a green Pinto...

14:23.082 --> 14:26.083
Minnesota license plate
TG0432--

14:26.438 --> 14:28.961
I was pouring sweat.

14:29.037 --> 14:31.234
My blood is too thick
for Nevada.

14:31.310 --> 14:34.121
I've never been able to properly
explain myself in this climate.

14:36.105 --> 14:38.954
Okay. Be quiet, be calm.

14:39.021 --> 14:42.598
Name, rank
and press affiliation.

14:42.665 --> 14:44.516
Nothing else.

14:44.583 --> 14:47.402
...hamburger stand.
She was a waitress about 16 years old.

14:47.469 --> 14:50.432
They chopped her goddamn head off right
there in the parking lot...

14:50.510 --> 14:52.514
and cut all kinds of holes in her
and sucked out the blood.

14:52.581 --> 14:55.966
They were after the pineal gland,
I think. Yeah.

14:56.043 --> 14:59.045
- No. How's your mama ?
ignore this terrible drug.

14:59.112 --> 15:00.934
Yeah.

15:01.001 --> 15:02.852
Pretend
it's not happening.

15:04.836 --> 15:07.493
Hi there ! Uhh--

15:07.560 --> 15:09.411
My name ?

15:09.478 --> 15:12.326
Uh...Raoul Duke !

15:12.393 --> 15:15.424
On the list.
Freelance. On the list, then ?

15:15.491 --> 15:17.985
Total coverage.
Uh-huh.

15:19.653 --> 15:22.473
I have my attorney...

15:24.582 --> 15:26.433
with me...

15:26.500 --> 15:29.319
and I realize that his name
is not on that list...

15:29.387 --> 15:31.238
but we must have
a suite !

15:32.293 --> 15:33.922
Must have that suite.

15:33.990 --> 15:35.841
What's the score here ?

15:35.908 --> 15:37.634
What's next ?

15:37.702 --> 15:39.744
Your suite isn't ready yet...

15:39.811 --> 15:42.688
but someone
was looking for you.

15:42.756 --> 15:45.028
Aah ! No ! We haven't done
anything yet !

15:45.095 --> 15:47.741
I can handle this.

15:47.819 --> 15:50.149
This man suffers
from a bad heart.

15:50.216 --> 15:53.438
But I have plenty of medicine.
My name is Dr. Gonzo.

15:53.505 --> 15:55.846
Prepare our suite at once.
We'll be in the bar.

16:00.775 --> 16:03.584
Aaah !

16:09.031 --> 16:12.321
I don't know about you,
but I'm startin' to feel that drink.

16:17.346 --> 16:19.686
Hey, beat it.
Beat it. Go on.

16:21.028 --> 16:22.880
I like the way you did that.

16:22.947 --> 16:24.806
Aaah !

16:24.864 --> 16:26.724
Come on.
Come on. Come on.

16:26.791 --> 16:29.602
- What's that ?
- Come on, come on.
Let's get some peanuts.

16:29.669 --> 16:32.479
That's one thing
that's good for you. Peanuts.

16:32.546 --> 16:34.521
Ohh ! Jesus !

16:34.598 --> 16:37.657
- Two Cuba libres, beer
and mescal on the side.
- You got it.

16:37.734 --> 16:40.065
I'll bet you're a Libra.
- Mmm.

16:46.978 --> 16:50.757
Who's Lacerda ? He's waiting
for us on the 12th floor.

16:50.814 --> 16:52.675
Room 1250. Lacerda.

16:53.826 --> 16:55.830
I couldn't remember.

16:55.907 --> 16:59.225
- The name rang a bell,
but I couldn't concentrate.

16:59.302 --> 17:01.632
Terrible things were happening
all around us.

17:03.137 --> 17:04.988
Buy us some golf shoes...

17:05.055 --> 17:08.700
otherwise we'll never
get out of this place alive.

17:08.767 --> 17:10.876
Impossible to walk
in this muck.

17:10.943 --> 17:12.804
No footing at all.

17:15.268 --> 17:19.038
Mr. Roger Pratt, please
call the hotel operator.

17:20.678 --> 17:25.655
<i>~ How can I bear
to see your heart break ~</i>

17:25.731 --> 17:27.964
<i>~ To see your heart break ~</i>

17:28.031 --> 17:31.197
<i>~ Over me ~</i>

17:54.108 --> 17:58.232
I was right in the middle
of a fucking reptile zoo...

17:58.299 --> 18:01.233
and somebody was giving booze
to these goddamn things.

18:01.310 --> 18:04.627
It won't be long now
before they tear us to shreds.

18:04.704 --> 18:06.872
[ Growling,
Roaring Continue ]

18:11.810 --> 18:14.841
[ Muttering, Roaring Continues,
Volume Increasing ]

18:18.303 --> 18:20.155
Please !

18:20.222 --> 18:24.018
- Tell'em to get out
their fucking golf shoes !

18:24.095 --> 18:26.905
Jesus God Almighty,
look at that bunch over there, man.

18:26.972 --> 18:28.823
They've spotted us.

18:28.890 --> 18:30.751
That's
the press table, man.

18:30.808 --> 18:33.628
We're gonna have to sign in
for our credentials.

18:34.970 --> 18:36.946
Okay ?

18:37.023 --> 18:38.615
Are you ready ?

18:38.682 --> 18:40.543
- Hmm ?
- Are you ready ?

18:41.693 --> 18:43.965
- Come on, hurry up.
- Wait ! Don't leave me !

18:46.488 --> 18:48.214
Two club sandwiches...

18:48.281 --> 18:51.599
and, uh,
two more club sandwiches...

18:51.676 --> 18:55.416
one, two, three, four
shrimp cocktails...

18:55.483 --> 18:57.334
- Hmm ? Hmm ?
- and nine fresh grapefruit.

18:57.402 --> 18:59.674
Vitamin C. Need all we can get.

18:59.741 --> 19:02.320
- Four chicken--
- There's a, uh...

19:02.397 --> 19:04.727
big machine in the sky,
some kind of...

19:04.795 --> 19:07.988
- Quart of rum.
- well, electric snake
coming straight at us.

19:08.055 --> 19:09.436
Shoot it.

19:09.503 --> 19:12.371
Not yet. I want
to study its habits.

19:12.438 --> 19:15.957
You motorcycle people
sure are hearty eaters.

19:16.025 --> 19:18.844
I need the cart.
I need to return with the cart.

19:18.911 --> 19:22.488
Thank you, but the cart needs to
go back with-- I'll be back !

19:22.555 --> 19:24.464
- You bastard.
- I've been hit, man !

19:24.540 --> 19:28.213
I leave you alone for 3 minutes
and you start waving that
goddamn marlin spike around...

19:28.280 --> 19:30.141
yelling about reptiles.

19:30.199 --> 19:33.267
- What are you talking about ?
- You scared the shit
out of those people.

19:33.334 --> 19:35.195
They were ready
to call the cops.

19:35.262 --> 19:39.664
- Yes, sir, you were lucky
I came back in time.
- Don't come fucking near me !

19:39.740 --> 19:42.770
Leave me alone.

19:42.837 --> 19:45.877
The only reason they gave us press
passes was to get you out of there.

19:46.807 --> 19:47.604
Oh, God ! What's that ?

19:47.671 --> 19:50.673
That scene straightened me
right out, man.

19:50.740 --> 19:54.039
Is it the door ?

19:54.107 --> 19:56.954
As the bombing continues in Laos--
- Just a minute.

19:57.012 --> 19:58.834
Holy shit.

19:58.901 --> 20:00.762
Oh, my God.

20:03.062 --> 20:07.321
Hi. I'm, uh, Lacerda,
your photographer.

20:12.020 --> 20:13.880
- Duke ?
- Mm-mmm.

20:13.948 --> 20:15.799
Back there.

20:15.866 --> 20:18.829
It looks as though
the North Vietnamese may--
- Duke ? Duke ?

20:18.906 --> 20:20.757
Hi !

20:20.824 --> 20:23.240
Lacerda.
Your photographer.

20:23.316 --> 20:25.177
You're not Portuguese, man !

20:25.235 --> 20:27.959
Hey, too bad you guys
missed the bikes checkin' in.

20:28.026 --> 20:29.876
Oh, man, what a sight !

20:29.943 --> 20:32.725
- Husquavarnas, Yamahas, DMZs.
- [ TV: Machine Guns Firing,
Volume Increasing ]

20:34.202 --> 20:36.139
Kawasakis !

20:36.215 --> 20:38.834
- Maicos. Pursang !
- [ TV: Plane Engines Roaring,
Volume Increasing ]

20:38.901 --> 20:41.395
Swedish fireballs.

20:41.462 --> 20:43.800
Couple of Triumphs.
Here and there a CZ.

20:43.858 --> 20:46.198
All very, very fast.

20:46.265 --> 20:48.117
Very.

20:48.184 --> 20:50.389
What a race
it's gonna be.

20:53.333 --> 20:56.632
Yeah.

21:00.497 --> 21:03.431
I'm gonna let myself out.

21:03.555 --> 21:05.282
We know what
you're up to, man.

21:05.349 --> 21:07.200
Hmm ?

21:10.432 --> 21:13.251
[ TV Continues: Explosions,
Helicopter Blades Whirring ]

21:16.129 --> 21:18.201
I'm gonna tell you--

21:18.277 --> 21:21.758
He's lying to us.
I could see it in his eyes.

21:21.825 --> 21:23.483
Eyes ?

21:23.550 --> 21:26.552
Late battle reports indicate--
- Panic now, Charlie.

21:28.548 --> 21:31.165
Turn this shit off.

21:36.450 --> 21:38.838
The racers were ready
at dawn.

21:38.915 --> 21:40.765
Very tense.

21:40.832 --> 21:44.217
In some circles the Mint 400
is a far, far better thing...

21:44.284 --> 21:47.161
than the Super Bowl,
the Kentucky Derby...

21:47.228 --> 21:50.048
and the Lower Oakland Roller
Derby Finals all rolled into one.

21:50.115 --> 21:51.966
Slow down !
This is a restricted area !

21:52.033 --> 21:54.306
This race attracts
a very special breed.

21:54.373 --> 21:56.310
Fuck off.
- All right.

21:56.387 --> 21:59.677
It was time to get grounded,
to ponder this rotten assignment...

21:59.744 --> 22:02.074
- and figure out how to cope with it.
- Whoa !

22:02.141 --> 22:04.001
It was time
to do the job.

22:04.068 --> 22:07.837
Those of us who had been
up all night were in no mood
for coffee and doughnuts.

22:07.904 --> 22:10.139
We wanted strong drink.

22:10.206 --> 22:12.067
We were, after all...

22:12.124 --> 22:14.099
the absolute cream
of the national sporting press.

22:14.176 --> 22:16.027
Pull !

22:16.094 --> 22:19.355
We were gathered in Las Vegas for
this very special moment in sport.

22:19.422 --> 22:22.241
- When it comes to a thing like
this, they don't fool around.

22:24.705 --> 22:27.515
It's, uh, just beautiful.

22:30.814 --> 22:33.145
Money plays. Money plays.

22:33.212 --> 22:36.473
Kill the body, the head will die.
Ali-Frazier fight.

22:36.540 --> 22:39.743
- Crazy shit.
- A proper end to the '60s.

22:39.810 --> 22:42.620
Ali beaten
by a human hamburger.

22:42.687 --> 22:45.400
- Both Kennedys murdered by mutants.
- Hey, they're startin' !

22:45.467 --> 22:47.328
Oh, shit, they're startin'.
Let's go !

22:47.386 --> 22:49.247
Ladies and gentlemen...

22:49.314 --> 22:53.562
welcome to the start of the
$50,000 Mint 400 Desert Race...

22:53.629 --> 22:56.794
with a purse of $50,000
going to the winner...

22:56.861 --> 22:59.288
of this grueling, gut-wrenching,
dust-eating...

22:59.355 --> 23:02.288
in-your-face
motocross extravaganza !

23:02.365 --> 23:04.216
And there they go !

23:04.283 --> 23:06.144
We've got
rooster tails goin' !

23:06.201 --> 23:08.982
We're here to spit
in your enemy's eye !

23:09.049 --> 23:11.188
There they go.

23:11.264 --> 23:14.707
All right, our second group
of ten is getting in place.

23:14.784 --> 23:17.939
Kawasakis, Triumphs, Maicos.

23:18.016 --> 23:21.170
We're ready to go. It's the green flag,
and they're off !

23:21.247 --> 23:24.345
Another great start with a lot of dirt
happening on this hill !

23:24.412 --> 23:28.056
All right, here we go with
the third group. And they're off !

23:28.123 --> 23:30.991
Number 45 riding
in the number-four position...

23:31.068 --> 23:33.657
is choking
as the dust flies !

23:33.724 --> 23:37.330
You'd better wet those bandannas
you got stretched over your face !

23:37.407 --> 23:39.257
[ Cheering,
Engines Revving ]

23:39.325 --> 23:42.134
There was something like
190 more bikes waiting to start.

23:42.201 --> 23:45.021
- Gimme a beer, man.
- They were due to go off,
ten at a time...

23:45.078 --> 23:46.939
every two minutes.

23:47.006 --> 23:48.857
There you go, buddy.

23:52.760 --> 23:55.484
-Goddamn it. What day is it ? Saturday ?
-Shit.

23:55.541 --> 23:57.402
- More like Sunday.
- Ahh.

24:01.659 --> 24:03.510
Hello ! Anyone ?

24:03.577 --> 24:05.428
Have you seen the race ?

24:05.495 --> 24:09.273
By 10:00 they were spread out
all over the course.

24:09.341 --> 24:11.508
- Ohh !
- It was no longer a race.

24:11.575 --> 24:14.549
Now it was
an endurance contest.

24:14.616 --> 24:18.931
The idea of trying to cover
this race in any conventional
press sense was absurd.

24:18.998 --> 24:21.299
- Hey ! It's pretty great, huh ?
- What ?

24:21.366 --> 24:23.371
Come on in !

24:27.802 --> 24:31.379
I'm just gonna try different
combinations of lenses and film...

24:31.446 --> 24:34.678
until I find something
that works in this dust !

24:36.662 --> 24:39.051
What the hell ?

24:39.127 --> 24:42.512
That's fucking machine guns.
They're firing at us. Machine guns !

24:42.579 --> 24:45.581
- It's a goddamn war zone !
Get us out of here quick !

24:45.658 --> 24:49.168
Yeee-hoo !
- Quick, man ! We're gonna
be killed, for fuck's sake !

24:49.235 --> 24:53.743
What the-- Oh, no.
Oh, God. Oh, God. Oh, God.

24:55.219 --> 24:57.080
Where's
the damn race ?

24:58.106 --> 24:59.956
Beats me, man.

25:00.023 --> 25:02.095
We're just good, patriotic Americans
like yourself.

25:03.283 --> 25:05.806
What outfit
you fellas with ?

25:05.873 --> 25:08.779
Oh. The sporting press.
We're friendlies.

25:08.856 --> 25:10.707
Hired geeks.

25:13.786 --> 25:16.115
Uh...yeah.

25:16.183 --> 25:19.530
- Let's go.
- Yee-ooooh !

25:19.606 --> 25:21.773
Good luck, gentlemen.

25:21.840 --> 25:23.700
- Get him !
- Freaks.

25:23.767 --> 25:26.702
- Take me back to the pits.
- No ! No, no, no. We have to go on.

25:26.769 --> 25:28.745
We need total coverage !

25:28.822 --> 25:32.811
It was time, I felt, for an agonizing
reappraisal of the whole scene.

25:32.888 --> 25:35.305
You're fired.

25:35.382 --> 25:37.136
Awful jackass.

25:38.614 --> 25:40.463
All right.

25:40.530 --> 25:43.053
- Just drive into the dust !
- I never wanna see you again.

25:43.120 --> 25:45.940
Just drive
into the dust !

25:46.007 --> 25:48.817
Huh ? Ohh.

25:51.541 --> 25:54.667
The race was
definitely underway.

25:54.744 --> 25:58.254
I had witnessed the start.
I was sure of that much.

25:58.321 --> 26:00.180
But what now ?

26:00.238 --> 26:02.099
What comes next ?

26:09.138 --> 26:11.958
Put on the radio.
Turn on the tape machine.

26:12.015 --> 26:13.875
Roll every
goddamn window down.

26:13.942 --> 26:16.273
<i>- ~ It's not unusual ~
- Let us taste this cool desert wind.</i>

26:16.340 --> 26:18.191
<i>~ To be loved by anyone ~</i>

26:18.259 --> 26:21.076
Ah, yes. This is what it's all about.

26:21.135 --> 26:22.995
Total control now...

26:23.062 --> 26:26.256
tooling along the main drag
on a Saturday night in Vegas.

26:26.323 --> 26:29.133
Two good old boys
in a fire-apple red convertible...

26:29.200 --> 26:33.065
stoned, ripped, twisted.

26:33.141 --> 26:34.993
Good people.

26:35.060 --> 26:37.639
Hot fuck.
That sounds heavy.

26:37.716 --> 26:40.458
- Twenty-nine cent hot dogs.
- Mmm.

26:40.525 --> 26:42.386
What are we doing here ?

26:42.453 --> 26:45.263
Are we here to entertain
ourselves or do the job ?

26:45.330 --> 26:47.535
Do the job, of course.

26:47.602 --> 26:51.660
Here we go. Crab louie and a quart
of muscatel for $20.

26:51.727 --> 26:56.464
<i>- ~ It's not unusual ~
- As your attorney, I advise you
to drive to the Tropicana.</i>

26:56.531 --> 26:59.341
Guy Lombardo. He's in the Blue Room
with his Royal Canadians.

26:59.408 --> 27:02.218
- Why ?
- Why ? Why what ?

27:02.285 --> 27:06.063
Why should I pay my hard-earned dollars
to watch a fucking corpse ?

27:06.131 --> 27:07.981
I don't know about you...

27:08.048 --> 27:11.175
- but in my line of business
it's important to be hep.

27:11.251 --> 27:12.901
What do you think
you're doing ?

27:12.978 --> 27:15.692
This is not a parking area !
You've got to move your car !

27:15.759 --> 27:18.579
You can't park your car here.
Excuse me. Sir !

27:18.637 --> 27:20.649
- What ?
- You can't park-- Hey !

27:20.716 --> 27:22.280
You can't
park your car here !

27:22.347 --> 27:24.840
Is this not
a reasonable place to park ?

27:24.907 --> 27:28.005
Reasonable ? You're on a sidewalk !
It's a sidewalk !

27:28.081 --> 27:29.933
- This is not a parking area !
- Debbie Reynolds ?

27:30.000 --> 27:33.289
- You can't park on the sidewalk !
- Seems like a hot ticket.

27:33.357 --> 27:36.013
Drove all the way from L.A.
for this show.

27:36.080 --> 27:37.605
We're friends
of Debbie's.

27:40.491 --> 27:42.352
- Okay, bye.
- We'll see you later.

27:42.409 --> 27:45.641
<i>This was Bob Hope's turf.
- ~ Strangers in the night ~</i>

27:45.708 --> 27:47.568
Frank Sinatra's.

27:47.626 --> 27:49.487
<i>- ~ Exchanging glances ~
- Spiro Agnew's.</i>

27:49.554 --> 27:53.773
The place fairly reeked of high-grade
Formica and plastic palm trees.

27:53.840 --> 27:57.101
Clearly a high-class refuge
for big spenders.

27:59.086 --> 28:02.116
- It's started. Is she on stage ?
- She is. Sold out.

28:02.193 --> 28:05.002
Sorry, sir. Full house.
I'm sorry, sir.

28:05.070 --> 28:07.880
We drove all the way
from L.A. for this show.

28:07.947 --> 28:11.246
- There are no seats left at any price.
- Fuck seats !

28:11.303 --> 28:14.602
- We're friends with Debbie.
I used to romp with her.
- Mm-hmm.

28:16.588 --> 28:19.656
- Are you prepared to go to court ?
- Well, that depends.

28:19.723 --> 28:22.543
I wanna talk to you
for a second.

28:22.600 --> 28:25.573
- Your attitude constitutes
a breach of faith.
- Uh, hi.

28:26.599 --> 28:28.459
In Nevada,
that's illegal.

28:29.640 --> 28:33.159
- What's your name ?
- My name ? Tony Pizzacata.

28:33.226 --> 28:35.077
Tony Pizzacata.

28:35.144 --> 28:37.484
What, may I ask, is your name, sir ?

28:37.551 --> 28:39.881
It's on my driver's license.

28:39.948 --> 28:42.758
- I think we might be able
to squeeze you in, sir.
- Ohh !

28:42.826 --> 28:45.711
- Thank you kindly.
- You'll have to stand in the back.

28:46.959 --> 28:50.737
After a lot of bad noise
he let us in for nothing...

28:50.795 --> 28:53.730
provided we would stand
quietly in the back and not smoke.

28:55.724 --> 28:57.585
Ladies and gentlemen...

28:57.642 --> 29:00.461
the Desert Inn is proud to present
the one, the only...

29:00.528 --> 29:03.492
the incomparable
Miss Debbie Reynolds !

29:03.568 --> 29:05.419
<i>~ Ooh, ooh-ooh ~</i>

29:05.486 --> 29:07.817
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen !

29:07.884 --> 29:10.703
It's wonderful to be here
with you fabulous people !

29:10.761 --> 29:14.146
Whoa !
Let's rock and roll !

29:14.223 --> 29:16.074
<i>~ Sgt. Pepper's
Lonely Hearts Club Band ~</i>

29:16.141 --> 29:18.470
What the hell's going on ?

29:18.538 --> 29:20.878
- Get'em out !
- Come on, get outta here !

29:20.945 --> 29:22.795
- Aah !
- Get'em out.

29:22.863 --> 29:25.989
<i>- ~ Ooooh, ooooh ~
- Out. Get'em out !</i>

29:26.056 --> 29:29.221
<i>~ Ooooh, ahhhh ~</i>

29:33.806 --> 29:37.249
Shit ! We wandered into a fuckin'
time capsule there.

29:37.325 --> 29:39.175
Scumbag !

29:39.242 --> 29:44.095
I'll find where you live and burn
your house down, you piece of shit !

29:44.172 --> 29:46.022
- What happened ?
- Oh.

29:46.089 --> 29:49.542
- Ohh.
- One of these days I'll toss
a fuckin' bomb in that place.

30:01.836 --> 30:04.320
Oh, wait. You see that ?

30:04.397 --> 30:06.247
This is the place, man.

30:06.315 --> 30:08.166
They'll never
fuck with us here.

30:09.671 --> 30:12.491
Where's the ether ?
Mescaline's not working.

30:12.558 --> 30:14.409
Oh.

30:16.394 --> 30:18.398
There we go.
Right.

30:22.982 --> 30:24.843
Yeah. Why not ?

30:26.597 --> 30:28.458
Yeah.

30:28.525 --> 30:30.376
Mm-hmm.

30:32.333 --> 30:35.775
Ahh. Devil ether.

30:35.852 --> 30:39.812
It makes you behave like the village
drunkard in some early Irish novel.

30:39.879 --> 30:42.210
Total loss of all
basic motor skills.

30:42.277 --> 30:45.097
Blurred vision,
no balance, numb tongue.

30:45.164 --> 30:47.100
The mind recoils in horror...

30:47.177 --> 30:49.987
unable to communicate
with the spinal column...

30:50.054 --> 30:53.833
which is interesting because
you can actually watch yourself
behaving in this terrible way...

30:53.900 --> 30:55.751
but you can't control it.

30:59.462 --> 31:02.847
You approach the turnstiles
and know that when you get there...

31:02.914 --> 31:05.734
you have to give the man two dollars
or he won't let you inside...

31:05.801 --> 31:09.627
but when you get there
everything goes wrong.

31:09.704 --> 31:13.895
Some angry Rotarian shoves you and
you think, "What's happening here ?"

31:13.962 --> 31:18.469
-You hear yourself mumbling:
-Dogs fucked the Pope. No fault of mine.

31:20.454 --> 31:23.551
Ether is the perfect drug
for Las Vegas.

31:23.619 --> 31:26.918
In this town they love a drunk.
Fresh meat.

31:26.985 --> 31:28.769
- Come on, buddy. Come on.
- Holy--

31:28.836 --> 31:32.835
So they put us through the turnstiles
and turned us loose inside.

31:32.902 --> 31:35.233
Ladies and gentlemen...

31:35.300 --> 31:37.160
boys and girls...

31:37.218 --> 31:40.516
visitors of all ages...

31:40.583 --> 31:45.628
- the Bazooko Casino Circus
proudly presents...

31:45.705 --> 31:48.898
the Flying Fellinis !

31:50.912 --> 31:53.636
Ooooh-whoop !

32:12.480 --> 32:14.340
Oh, my God !

32:15.875 --> 32:17.724
Whoop !

32:35.717 --> 32:37.336
<i>~ Mm-hmm ~</i>

32:49.152 --> 32:50.676
Whoa !

32:51.807 --> 32:53.333
Excuse me.

32:53.410 --> 32:56.440
