Eat some reds and try to calm down.

48:59.073 --> 49:01.892
Smoke some grass.
Shoot some fucking smack.

49:01.949 --> 49:05.248
Shit, man, do whatever
you gotta do, but please...

49:05.315 --> 49:08.662
I need some fucking rest,
man. Please. Please.

49:08.739 --> 49:11.222
Get out of here,
you pig fucker !

49:11.299 --> 49:14.263
Up ! Up !

49:14.339 --> 49:17.149
Well, l, uh--

49:17.217 --> 49:19.068
Yeah.

49:20.190 --> 49:22.712
You need to get to work.

49:22.789 --> 49:24.860
Goddamn, what a bummer.

49:24.927 --> 49:26.788
You scurvy
shyster bastard.

49:26.845 --> 49:29.464
I'm a Doctor of Journalism, man.

49:29.540 --> 49:31.390
Go on.

49:31.457 --> 49:33.462
- Don't let me keep you up.
- Now--

49:33.539 --> 49:36.636
Don't let me keep you up.

49:36.703 --> 49:39.523
Get in there and clean your shorts !

49:39.581 --> 49:42.332
Clean your shorts, goddamn it,
like a big boy !

49:42.399 --> 49:44.251
Pig !

49:47.003 --> 49:49.823
The acid had
shifted gears on him.

49:49.890 --> 49:53.658
The next phase would probably be
one of those hellishly intense
introspective nightmares.

49:53.725 --> 49:55.585
Must get some peace.

49:55.643 --> 49:58.741
Four hours or so of catatonic despair.

49:58.817 --> 50:01.781
- Damn drugs.
- Aaaaah !

50:02.203 --> 50:05.205
Mmm ?

50:07.650 --> 50:11.227
Ignore the nightmare
in the bathroom.

50:11.294 --> 50:14.420
Just another ugly refugee
from the love generation.

50:15.743 --> 50:18.525
My attorney had never been
able to accept the notion...

50:18.592 --> 50:20.922
often espoused
by former drug abusers...

50:20.990 --> 50:24.116
that you can get a lot higher
without drugs than with them.

50:24.193 --> 50:26.043
Neither have l,
for that matter.

50:26.110 --> 50:28.892
<i>~ When the truth is found ~</i>

50:28.959 --> 50:33.178
<i>~ To be lies ~</i>

50:33.245 --> 50:35.796
<i>~ And all the joy ~</i>

50:35.872 --> 50:40.179
<i>~ Within you dies ~</i>

50:40.256 --> 50:42.902
<i>~ Don't you want
somebody to love ~</i>

50:42.969 --> 50:46.383
<i>~ Don't you need
somebody to love ~</i>

50:46.460 --> 50:49.845
<i>~ Wouldn't you love
somebody to love ~</i>

50:49.914 --> 50:54.736
<i>~ You better find
somebody to love ~</i>

50:54.813 --> 50:56.722
<i>~ Love ~</i>

50:58.716 --> 51:02.811
1965.
The great San Francisco acid wave.

51:02.878 --> 51:04.950
<i>~ When the garden flowers ~</i>

51:05.017 --> 51:09.754
I recall one night in a place
called the Matrix. There I was--

51:09.821 --> 51:13.110
Mother of God. There I am.

51:13.177 --> 51:15.038
Holy fuck.

51:15.095 --> 51:19.219
Uh, clearly I was a victim
of the drug explosion...

51:19.286 --> 51:22.873
a natural street freak
just eating whatever came by.

51:22.940 --> 51:27.697
Does anybody want some LSD ?

51:27.774 --> 51:31.187
I got all the makin's...

51:31.254 --> 51:33.844
right here !

51:33.911 --> 51:39.511
All I need is a place to cook.

51:42.456 --> 51:45.870
I decided to eat only
half of the acid at first...

51:45.946 --> 51:49.591
but I spilled the rest on the sleeve
of my red woolen shirt.

51:53.723 --> 51:57.617
What's the trouble ?

51:57.685 --> 52:00.590
Well, all this white stuff...

52:00.667 --> 52:03.630
on my sleeve...

52:04.916 --> 52:08.847
is LSD.

52:23.251 --> 52:24.882
With a bit of luck...

52:26.071 --> 52:27.730
his life
was ruined forever...

52:27.797 --> 52:32.399
always thinking that just behind some
narrow door in all his favorite bars...

52:32.467 --> 52:34.644
men in red woolen shirts...

52:34.711 --> 52:38.490
are getting incredible kicks
from things he'll never know.

52:43.955 --> 52:47.504
Strange memories on
this nervous night in Las Vegas.

52:47.571 --> 52:52.011
Has it been five years ? Six ?

52:52.088 --> 52:57.007
It seems like a lifetime, the kind
of peak that never comes again.

52:57.074 --> 52:59.980
<i>~ Love is but
a song we're singin' ~</i>

53:00.057 --> 53:02.445
San Francisco
in the middle '60s...

53:02.522 --> 53:06.291
was a very special time and place
to be a part of...

53:06.358 --> 53:08.909
<i>- but no explanation...
- ~ We can make the mountains ring ~</i>

53:08.986 --> 53:10.835
no mix of words
or music or memories...

53:10.902 --> 53:14.249
can touch that sense of knowing
that you were there and alive...

53:14.326 --> 53:18.125
in that corner of time in the world,
whatever it meant.

53:18.201 --> 53:21.779
<i>~ Though the bird
is on the wing ~</i>

53:21.846 --> 53:25.289
<i>~ And you may not
know why ~</i>

53:27.120 --> 53:28.981
There was madness
in any direction...

53:29.048 --> 53:31.243
<i>- ~ Come on, people, now ~
- at any hour.</i>

53:31.319 --> 53:33.324
<i>- ~ Smile on your brothers ~
- You could strike sparks anywhere.</i>

53:33.391 --> 53:35.693
<i>~ Everybody get together ~</i>

53:35.760 --> 53:37.774
<i>- ~ Try to love one another ~
- There was a fantastic
universal sense...</i>

53:37.841 --> 53:40.210
that whatever we were doing was right,
that we were winning.

53:41.332 --> 53:43.538
And that, I think,
was the handle.

53:43.605 --> 53:45.360
<i>~ Some may come
and some may go ~</i>

53:45.427 --> 53:47.278
That sense
of inevitable victory...

53:47.345 --> 53:48.842
over the forces
of old and evil.

53:48.918 --> 53:52.015
Not in any mean or military sense--
we didn't need that.

53:53.942 --> 53:56.522
Our energy
would simply prevail.

53:56.599 --> 53:59.697
We had all the momentum.

53:59.764 --> 54:03.111
We were riding the crest
of a high and beautiful wave.

54:04.559 --> 54:09.200
So now, less than five years later...

54:09.267 --> 54:12.710
you can go up a steep hill
in Las Vegas and look west...

54:12.787 --> 54:15.308
and with the right kind
of eyes...

54:15.376 --> 54:18.310
you can almost see
the high-water mark...

54:18.387 --> 54:21.197
that place where the wave
finally broke...

54:21.264 --> 54:23.125
and rolled back.

54:23.183 --> 54:26.961
<i>~ Try to love one another right now ~</i>

54:34.603 --> 54:36.944
<i>~ [ Piano Continues,
Rock Band Begins ]</i>

54:37.011 --> 54:39.341
<i>~ Want some whiskey in your water ~</i>

54:39.409 --> 54:42.439
<i>- Room service !
- ~ Some sugar in your tea ~</i>

54:42.516 --> 54:45.613
<i>~ What's all these crazy questions
they're askin' me ~</i>

54:45.681 --> 54:48.490
<i>- Good morning, sir.
- ~ This is the craziest party
there could ever be ~</i>

54:48.557 --> 54:51.376
What do you want, man ?
What do you want ?

54:51.443 --> 54:53.294
- Room service.
- Get out.

54:53.361 --> 54:56.172
<i>- ~ Mama told me not to come ~
- You're in the wrong room.
Get the fuck out !</i>

54:56.239 --> 54:59.057
<i>- I've got a gun. It's not mine, really.
- ~ Mama told me not to come ~</i>

54:59.115 --> 55:00.976
- Uh, the-- the-- the bill.
- What ?

55:01.043 --> 55:03.853
- Will you...s-sign for it ?
- Yeah, I'll get it. Hurry up.

55:03.920 --> 55:06.251
Don't move, man.
Be very still.

55:06.318 --> 55:08.178
There we go.

55:08.236 --> 55:10.096
Say nothing
to no one, man.

55:10.163 --> 55:13.193
<i>~ Open up the window
Let some air into this room ~</i>

55:13.261 --> 55:17.518
The decision
to flee came suddenly. Or maybe not.

55:17.586 --> 55:21.479
<i>- ~ That cigarette you're smokin'
'bout scared me half to death ~
- Maybe I'd planned it all along,</i>

55:21.546 --> 55:23.819
subconsciously waiting
for the right moment.

55:23.887 --> 55:26.639
<i>- ~ Mama told me not to come ~
- The bill was a factor, I think...</i>

55:26.706 --> 55:29.380
<i>- because I had no money to pay for it.
- ~ Mama told me not to come ~</i>

55:29.457 --> 55:33.227
Our room service tabs had been
running somewhere between
29 and 36 dollars per hour...

55:33.294 --> 55:36.103
<i>- ~ That ain't the way
to have fun, son ~
- for 48 consecutive hours.</i>

55:36.170 --> 55:38.031
<i>- Incredible.
- ~ That ain't the way to have fun ~</i>

55:38.089 --> 55:39.950
How could it happen ?

55:40.017 --> 55:44.207
But by the time I asked this question,
there was no one around to answer it.

55:44.265 --> 55:47.267
That rotten attorney of mine,
Dr. Gonzo, was gone.

55:47.344 --> 55:49.193
He must have sensed trouble.

55:49.260 --> 55:51.016
Hmm ? Ohh.

55:51.083 --> 55:52.837
A "Z" ?

55:52.904 --> 55:54.880
Panic.

55:55.178 --> 55:59.589
It crept up my spine like
first-rising vibes of an acid frenzy.

55:59.656 --> 56:03.435
- All these horrible realities
began to dawn on me.

56:03.503 --> 56:06.120
Oh, fuck.

56:06.187 --> 56:08.038
Here I was...

56:08.105 --> 56:11.039
alone in Las Vegas,
completely twisted on drugs.

56:11.116 --> 56:14.281
No cash,
no story for the magazine...

56:14.348 --> 56:19.565
and on top of everything else
I had a gigantic goddamn
hotel bill to deal with.

56:21.895 --> 56:24.197
I didn't even know
who'd won the race.

56:24.265 --> 56:26.125
Maybe nobody.

56:26.182 --> 56:29.001
How would Horatio Alger
have handled this situation ?

56:30.124 --> 56:33.287
Stay calm.
Stay calm.

56:33.355 --> 56:35.589
I'm a relatively
respectable citizen.

56:35.657 --> 56:38.563
- Multiple felon, perhaps,
but certainly not dangerous.

56:38.630 --> 56:40.970
Taxi !

56:41.037 --> 56:45.372
Luckily I had taken the soap
and grapefruit and other luggage
out to the car earlier.

56:45.448 --> 56:46.915
Now--

56:46.983 --> 56:48.842
it was only a matter
of slipping the noose.

56:48.900 --> 56:52.544
Hey ! Here, take this.
All right.

56:52.621 --> 56:56.543
- Mr. Duke ! Mr. Duke !
- Oh, shit.

56:56.620 --> 57:00.745
- We've been looking for you.
- The game was up. They had me.

57:00.812 --> 57:03.977
Many fine books have been written
in prison, huh ?

57:04.044 --> 57:06.143
- Sir ?
- What ?

57:06.220 --> 57:08.224
Um, this telegram
came for you.

57:08.301 --> 57:11.168
Actually, it's not for you.
It's for somebody named, uh, Thompson.

57:11.235 --> 57:14.467
But it says, "Care of Raoul Duke."
Do you-- Do you--

57:14.534 --> 57:17.402
- Does that mean anything ?
- Yes, yes, it means a lot. Thanks.

57:17.479 --> 57:20.778
- Yeah, I checked the register
for this man Thompson.

57:20.835 --> 57:23.290
We don't show him, but I figured
he might be part of your team.

57:23.367 --> 57:25.314
-He is. Don't worry. I'll get it to him.
-Yeah.

57:25.381 --> 57:27.902
Um, what confused us
was, uh...

57:27.979 --> 57:32.227
Dr. Gonzo's signature
on the telegram from Los Angeles
when we knew he was right here.

57:32.295 --> 57:34.338
Right.
You did the right thing.

57:34.405 --> 57:37.608
Never try to understand a press message.
About half the time, we use codes.

57:37.675 --> 57:39.871
Especially with Dr. Gonzo.
See ya.

57:39.938 --> 57:43.649
Um, tell me.

57:43.716 --> 57:46.172
When will the doctor
be awake ?

57:46.248 --> 57:50.074
- Awake ? What do you mean ?
- Well, um...

57:50.150 --> 57:53.661
my manager, Mr. Heem,
would like to meet him.

57:53.737 --> 57:56.126
It's nothing unusual, um--

57:56.193 --> 58:00.057
Mr. Heem likes to meet
all of our large accounts...

58:00.134 --> 58:02.302
put'em on a personal basis,
you know ?

58:02.369 --> 58:04.479
Just a chat and a handshake.
You understand.

58:04.546 --> 58:06.406
Of course,
but if I were you...

58:06.473 --> 58:08.774
I would leave the doctor alone
until after he's eaten his breakfast...

58:08.832 --> 58:10.692
because he's
a very crude man.

58:10.759 --> 58:13.119
Jesus God !

58:13.186 --> 58:15.574
No !

58:15.651 --> 58:20.225
But he will be available,
huh, maybe later this morning ?

58:20.292 --> 58:24.157
Look, the telegram
is actually all scrambled.

58:24.224 --> 58:27.072
It's actually from Thompson,
not to him.

58:27.140 --> 58:30.649
All right ? Now, I've got to go.
I've gotta get to the race.

58:30.725 --> 58:33.344
- B-But there's no hurry.
The race is over.
- Not for me.

58:33.411 --> 58:36.441
Well, um--
Let's have lunch !

58:36.518 --> 58:38.906
Righty-o, man.
Righty-o.

58:39.232 --> 58:44.468
<i>- ~ Now, the bricks
lay on Grand Street ~
- Jesus.</i>

58:44.545 --> 58:49.282
Bad waves of paranoia.
Madness. Fear and loathing.

58:49.349 --> 58:52.131
Intolerable vibrations
in this place. Get out.

58:52.198 --> 58:54.048
The weasels were closing in.

58:54.115 --> 58:56.254
I could smell the ugly brutes.

58:56.321 --> 58:58.172
Do me one last favor, Lord.

58:58.239 --> 59:01.653
Just give me five more high-speed hours
before You bring the hammer down.

59:01.731 --> 59:06.679
Just let me get rid of this goddamn car
and off this horrible desert.

59:06.756 --> 59:10.466
<i>~ Oh, Mama ~</i>

59:10.533 --> 59:13.756
<i>~ Is this really the end ~</i>

59:13.823 --> 59:16.374
<i>- ~ To be stuck inside of Mobile ~
- Oh, you evil bastard.</i>

59:16.451 --> 59:18.935
<i>- ~ With the Memphis blues again ~
- This is Your work.
You better take care of me, Lord.</i>

59:19.011 --> 59:21.696
- If You don't, You're
gonna have me on Your hands.

59:30.940 --> 59:33.434
- Pull over ! Pull over !
- Hey !

59:33.501 --> 59:34.968
Good morning. How are you ?
All right, man. Doing very well.

59:39.582 --> 59:41.557
Few people understand the psychology
of dealing with a highway traffic cop.

59:41.633 --> 59:45.979
Your normal speeder will panic
and immediately pull over to the side.

59:46.046 --> 59:48.912
This is wrong.
It arouses contempt in the cop heart.

59:50.427 --> 59:53.563
Make the bastard chase you.
He will follow.

59:53.630 --> 59:57.208
But he won't know what to make
of your blinker signal that says
you're about to turn right.

59:57.275 --> 01:00:01.849
This is to let him know you're
pulling off for a proper place to talk.

01:00:01.916 --> 01:00:04.074
It'll take him a moment
to realize he's about to make
a 180-degree turn, at speed.

01:00:04.074 --> 01:00:06.338
It'll take him a moment
to realize he's about to make
a 180-degree turn, at speed.

01:00:06.405 --> 01:00:08.513
But you will be ready.
Brace for the "G"s.

01:00:08.580 --> 01:00:10.595
Fast heel-toe work.

01:00:22.660 --> 01:00:25.411
Hi. How are you ?

01:00:27.559 --> 01:00:30.340
Just what in the hell
did you think you were doing ?

01:00:30.408 --> 01:00:33.668
I wanna know.
Let me see your license.

01:00:33.735 --> 01:00:36.670
Oh, yeah, of course.
There you are.

01:00:39.653 --> 01:00:41.513
Oh, my gosh.

01:00:45.800 --> 01:00:48.033
It's me.

01:00:48.101 --> 01:00:49.952
May I please have that ?

01:00:51.400 --> 01:00:54.018
I knew I was fucked.

01:00:59.782 --> 01:01:03.100
See you have two cases of beer,
a basket of grapefruit...

01:01:03.177 --> 01:01:05.440
stack of T-shirts and towels,
light bulbs.

01:01:07.271 --> 01:01:10.685
- You realize what you did
when you drive like that ?
- Yeah, I know. I'm guilty.

01:01:10.752 --> 01:01:14.138
I understand that. I knew it
was a crime. I did it anyway.

01:01:14.214 --> 01:01:17.063
Shit, why argue ?
I'm a fucking criminal. Look at me.

01:01:17.120 --> 01:01:19.546
You have
a strange attitude.

01:01:19.623 --> 01:01:21.560
Maybe.

01:01:21.637 --> 01:01:25.943
You know, I have a feeling
you need to take a nap.

01:01:26.020 --> 01:01:28.225
There's a rest area
just up ahead.

01:01:28.292 --> 01:01:31.390
I'd like you to go up there,
pull over and get a few hours' sleep.

01:01:31.457 --> 01:01:33.404
That's not gonna help me.

01:01:33.471 --> 01:01:36.539
I've been awake for too long.
Three or four nights, maybe.
Can't even remember.

01:01:36.606 --> 01:01:39.225
I go to sleep now,
I'm dead for 20 hours.

01:01:40.673 --> 01:01:43.455
What are you carrying
two cases of soap for, son ?

01:01:43.522 --> 01:01:45.861
I wanna stay clean.

01:01:45.919 --> 01:01:47.779
No.

01:01:49.054 --> 01:01:50.752
Here's how it is.

01:01:50.819 --> 01:01:53.600
What I put in my book,
as of noon...

01:01:53.667 --> 01:01:56.793
is that I apprehended you
for driving too fast.

01:01:56.870 --> 01:01:59.996
- I advised you to proceed
to the next rest area.

01:02:00.063 --> 01:02:01.924
Stop !

01:02:04.926 --> 01:02:07.745
I advised you to proceed
to the next rest area--

01:02:07.812 --> 01:02:10.709
your stated destination, right ?

01:02:12.223 --> 01:02:14.717
And take a long nap.

01:02:15.868 --> 01:02:18.208
Do I make myself clear ?

01:02:18.275 --> 01:02:21.143
Well...
how far is Baker ?

01:02:21.219 --> 01:02:24.480
I was sort of hoping to,
I don't know, stop there for lunch.

01:02:25.889 --> 01:02:27.740
It's not my jurisdiction.

01:02:27.807 --> 01:02:31.192
City limits end 2.2 miles
beyond the rest area.

01:02:31.260 --> 01:02:33.148
Can you make it that far ?

01:02:33.215 --> 01:02:35.287
I'll try.

01:02:35.364 --> 01:02:39.449
I've been wanting to go to Baker for
a long time. Yeah. Heard a lot about it.

01:02:41.214 --> 01:02:43.074
Excellent seafood.

01:02:44.801 --> 01:02:47.927
You know, I'm thinkin',
a guy with your kind of mind...

01:02:48.003 --> 01:02:50.745
ought to try
the land-crab.

01:02:50.814 --> 01:02:54.073
- Excellent seafood.
- Land-crab.

01:02:54.140 --> 01:02:57.334
All right. Why not ?

01:02:57.401 --> 01:02:59.607
Thanks for the tip.

01:02:59.674 --> 01:03:01.689
Look at me in the eyes.

01:03:04.863 --> 01:03:06.713
Everything all right ?

01:03:09.887 --> 01:03:13.464
May I have a little kiss
before you go ?

01:03:13.531 --> 01:03:16.984
I'm very lonely here.

01:03:17.233 --> 01:03:20.369
<i>~ Oh, Mama ~</i>

01:03:20.436 --> 01:03:23.122
<i>~ Can this really
be the end ~</i>

01:03:23.189 --> 01:03:26.899
I felt raped.
The pig had done me on all fronts.

01:03:26.967 --> 01:03:30.026
And now he was going off to chuckle
about it on the west side of town...

01:03:30.103 --> 01:03:32.462
waiting for me
to make a run for L.A.

01:03:32.529 --> 01:03:36.557
Why, yes, Officer. Of course
I'll take advantage of that rest area.

01:03:36.624 --> 01:03:41.064
And I can't tell you how grateful
I am for this break you wanna give me.

01:03:41.141 --> 01:03:43.951
Get a grip, man.

01:03:44.018 --> 01:03:47.431
If I boom straight for L.A.,
he'll bust me for sure.

01:03:47.508 --> 01:03:50.951
No. This was not the time
for a showdown.

01:03:53.109 --> 01:03:55.114
This was Death Valley.

01:03:57.549 --> 01:03:59.889
Oh, fuck !

01:03:59.957 --> 01:04:02.259
Sweet Jesus, it's him.

01:04:02.326 --> 01:04:04.655
Oh, my God !

01:04:09.613 --> 01:04:13.037
Shit !
Come on, you fucking bastard.

01:04:13.104 --> 01:04:16.202
Oh, God. Oh, God. Oh, God.
I've got to go. I've got to--

01:04:18.734 --> 01:04:20.910
Well, they've nailed me,
goddamn it.

01:04:20.977 --> 01:04:23.308
I'm trapped in some stinking
desert crossroads called Baker.

01:04:23.375 --> 01:04:26.031
I don't have much time, man.
The fuckers are closing in.

01:04:26.098 --> 01:04:29.158
- They'll hunt me down
like a fucking beast.
You sound paranoid.

01:04:29.234 --> 01:04:31.238
I need a fucking lawyer
immediately !

01:04:31.315 --> 01:04:33.962
What are you doing in Baker ?
Didn't you get my telegram ?

01:04:34.029 --> 01:04:38.344
What telegram, you worthless bastard ?
I'll cripple your ass for this.

01:04:38.412 --> 01:04:41.481
You brainless scumbag,
you're supposed to be in Vegas.

01:04:41.548 --> 01:04:43.629
I rented a suite
at the Flamingo.

01:04:43.696 --> 01:04:47.886
